Maintainer: Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: raidutils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Adaptec I2O hardware RAID controller management utilities
 The raidutil programs manage some I2O-compliant RAID controllers, in
 particular some Adaptec hardware.  One can create/delete a RAID
 array, add/remove a hot spare drive to/from a RAID array,
 activate/silence the alarm, and get information about the status of
 the RAID array and disks.
